Description: Full Trinity Desktop Environment, curated (metapackage)
 A custom metapackage that installs a complete Trinity Desktop Environment
 (TDE) on Debian, built as an independent alternative to the stock
 tde-trinity, redmond-default-settings-trinity and
 redmond-default-settings-ii-trinity metapackages.
 .
 Compared to the stock metapackages, this package:
  - drops legacy/no-longer-needed components (kfloppy, k3b, cvs/cervisia
    and the rest of the tdesdk dev-tools module, lisa/kpf network
    discovery, tdebindings, and similar cruft)
  - does not force the "Redmond" Windows-like default look-and-feel
  - adds modern desktop-stack integration: plymouth, pipewire-audio,
    xsettingsd, xdg-desktop-portal-trinity, polkitd/polkit-agent-tde,
    tdesudo, network-manager/network-manager-tde, tdebluez-trinity,
    tde-ebook-reader and kdbusnotification-trinity
 .
 This package intentionally does not depend on the stock tde-trinity or
 redmond-default-settings(-ii)-trinity packages, so it can be installed
 without pulling in their unwanted dependencies.
